  "body": "Plan\r\n\r\n- [x] Refactor the current stateless API into a session-based stateful API to track changes\r\n- [ ] Prototype implementation highlighting the new API usage integrated in UX (new on top)\r\n- [ ] Try the SQL filer approach\r\n- [ ] Show new entry notification (scenario 3)\r\n- [ ] Merge new entries API (scenarios 1 & 3)\r\n- [ ] Highlight hidden (unfiltered entries, scenarios 3 & 4)\r\n- [ ] UX - Scenario 01: No activity filter applied, New Txs loading in are the most recent (new button)\r\n- [ ] UX - Scenario 02: No activity filter applied, New Tx loading in is NOT the most recent\r\n- [ ] UX - Scenario 03:  Activity filter applied, New Txs loading in are the most recent but only one applies to current filter (new button and filter clear)\r\n- [ ] UX - Scenario 04: Activity filter applied, New Tx loading in is the most recent but doesnâ€™t apply to current filter (filer clear)\r\n- [ ] Refactor the async handling to fit the session based better (use channels and goroutine)\r\nand cleanup old code\r\n\r\nScenarios 3 and 4 cover what happens if there are Tx's that come in while the Activity view is filtered\r\nAll of the design flows covering the scenarios when new transactions come in are here:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?type=design&node-id=14883-444030&mode=design&t=fJuL9i0YOoayf4VU-4\r\n\r\n![hillchart-January-23-2024_11_40](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/47554641/a1375d5c-25be-43f8-b4a7-1f237e276ec3)",
